description:
## Overview
Create `pkg/agents/detect.go` as the single source of truth for which agent config directories maestro manages, and detection of which ones are present in a project.

## Context
Both `cmd/update.go` and `cmd/doctor.go` need to know which agent config directories are present. This package centralizes that knowledge to avoid duplication and ensure consistency.

## Implementation Details

```go
package agents

import "os"

// KnownAgentDirs returns the complete list of agent config directories
// that maestro can manage. This is the single source of truth.
func KnownAgentDirs() []string {
    return []string{".opencode", ".claude"}
}

// DetectInstalled returns the subset of KnownAgentDirs that exist
// as directories under projectRoot.
func DetectInstalled(projectRoot string) []string {
    var installed []string
    for _, dir := range KnownAgentDirs() {
        path := filepath.Join(projectRoot, dir)
        if info, err := os.Stat(path); err == nil && info.IsDir() {
            installed = append(installed, dir)
        }
    }
    return installed
}
```

**Files:**
- `cmd/maestro-cli/pkg/agents/detect.go` — create new file (new package `agents`)

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] `KnownAgentDirs()` returns exactly `[".opencode", ".claude"]`
- [ ] `DetectInstalled()` returns only dirs that exist as directories on disk
- [ ] `go build ./...` passes

